 A law firm, Hybrid Solicitors, will hold its eighth annual lecture/luncheon on December 17. Its theme is Global mobility and taxation of expatriates in Nigeria. The Practice Manager, Victoria Agomuo, said in a statement that the annual lecture, which is part of its Corporate Social Responsibility, provides a forum for continuing legal education.  According to her, the event, to be held at the Oriental Hotel, Victoria Island, promises to be an exciting learning experience. 